Yeah there is, I have a small wiki on this project page that has a bit of [documentation on that](https://github.com/alex-sherman/deco/wiki/@concurrent#custom-parameters). All of the keyword arguments passed to `@concurrent` get passed to the constructor of a `multiprocessing.Pool`. So it's really just:

```python
@concurrent(processes=2)
def work():
    ...
```

